revisions.comment: /* History */ in fact, adding fv tag as all I can find in the source provided is the following non-descriptive statement: "Gottfried Wilhelm Leibniz – whilst he did not invent a computer as such he was an early inventor of a calculating machine, though not the first. Many of you will be aware of Leibniz’s work...if you want to know more, and have your Latin knowledge at the ready, do please come and have a look."

/* History */ in fact, nowhere in the target page does it say that Leibniz's Stepped reckoner was based on binary. "Digital" refers to based on a series of digits - often binary, but I am not sure that it is always the case.
Included "(binary-based)" to specify that here "digital" refers to a binary-based system, and not the digital screens that most people tend to associate with the word.
